        console.log(urls); // output the URLs to the console or save them to a file or database as needed
      });
  });
```
This script first makes a search request using the `axios.get()` method, passing in the necessary parameters for fetching search results based on our desired search term, site, and tags (if provided). It then extracts the list of question IDs from the search results and makes a second request using `axios.get()` again to fetch the details of those specific questions, including their URLs, based on their IDs. Finally, it extracts the URLs of those questions and outputs them to the console for further processing or storage as needed. Note that you'll need to replace some of the hardcoded values in this script (such as `searchTerm`, `siteName`, and `tags`) with your specific values for your desired search query and StackOverflow site(s). Also note that this script assumes you're searching only one site at a time (`stackoverflow` in this case), but you can easily modify it to support searching multiple sites by appending their respective names to the `site` parameter in both search requests.

